* are burrowing insectivores, though they don't pass up earthworms, small lizards, frogs, mice, or whatever else they can catch, even the occasional snake if it isn't too big for them
* spend a lot of time in their burrows
* are solitary, not very social
* are nocturnal, usually sleeping all day in their burrows and come out to feed at night
* have poor eyesight but a good sense of smell, a good sense of hearing, and seem to be able to detect insects underground by sensing vibrations through the soil
* really hate strong smells
* are related to sloths, sharing the low body temperature and slow metabolism
* are easily startled, some species demonstrating a startle reflex in which they leap 3-4 feet into the air
* some species roll into a ball when startled
* can spray foul-smelling fluids from glands near the anus, like skunks
* despite all of this tend to be relatively docile, as they don't have many natural predators
* behavior can seem crazy to human observers, but they're actually clever, and working from limited sensory data--poor eyesight
* like to live near water, especially running water
* can scuttle along on their stubby little legs MUCH faster than you'd think, and are very good swimmers too
* one page says that some species are smart enough to use tools but gave no details and I can't find any other page attributing that to them
